                    h2.section-heading.text-uppercase How does it work?
                .row.justify-content-center
                    .col-6
                        p.text-muted 
                            | The OGC API - Tiles Standard describes how mapping clients (e.g.: web pages, desktop applications) can get information about tilesets and how to request the tiled data itself.
                            | Like the
                            a(href="https://docs.mapbox.com/help/glossary/tilejson/" target="_blank") TileJSON
                            | specification, implementations of the OCG API - Tiles Standard provides a way to describe tilesets available on a server.  
                            | At the same time, it supports more use cases, such as serving data which is not projected in Google Mercator.
                            | Unlike the OGC Web Map Tiling Service Standard
                            a(href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Web_Map_Tile_Service" target="_blank") (WMTS)
                            | , the Tiles API specifies the use of JSON instead of XML and is organized in a series of
                            a(href="https://blocks.ogc.org" target="_blank") building blocks 
                            | that can be easily integrated into other applications.
                            | These building blocks are mapped to conformance classes. 
                            | One may choose to conform to one or more conformance classes, according to the complexity of the use case and the aimed degree of interoperability.
                            br
                            a(href="standard.html" target="_blank") Learn more                            

